    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "May\nEighteenth,\n1 9 2 7\n!\nMr. Iloyd H. Berendsen,\n1517 Lake St.,\nSan Francisco.\nDear Sir:\nIn line with its policy to obtain data to enable it to\nsecure the best possible location for a municipal air port,\nand. County\nof San Francisco would like to locate on Varney\n1ield, as per the enclosed map, a temporary\npurpose of\nsecuring meteorological\ndata.\nstructure for the\nThe work will be in\ncharge of men assigned from the United States Weather Bureau and\nperiod\nof observation will be from July 1, 1927, to June 30,\n1928.\nour desire to commence\nthe construction\nnecessary building and installation of the necessary instruments\nimmediately.\nWe would appreciate very much permission from the owners\nand lessees\nthe Varney field\nto locate the meteorological\nstation on this field, as per the map enclosed, with the privilege\nof access to\ncourse, it would be understood that in\nthe event that the owners sold the property before\nJune 30, 1928,\nthat the privilege would cease, and that upon a thirty day notice\nfrom the owners\nthat we would remove the structure.\nWe also\ndesire the privilege of removing\nthe structure and instruments at\nthe expiration of the observation period.\nI am enclosing a letter for the owners and lessees to\nsign.\nThanking you in advance for any courtesies you may extend\nto us, I\nam\nVery truly yours,\nRIGHT OF WAY AGENT.\nJJP :KH"
